    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Heineken Division Picks Joint Venture</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Stuart Elliott</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Elliott, Stuart</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Heineken Latin America and Caribbean in Miami, unit of Heineken NV, names new agencies to handle creative portion of its account (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Heineken Latin America and Caribbean in Miami, a unit of Heineken N.V., has named a joint venture of Upmarket Illustra in San Francisco and Burkhardt &amp; Partners in New York to handle the creative portion of its account, with billings estimated at $10 million over three years. Those duties had been handled on a project basis by Upmarket, which is headed by Robert Gordon.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Heineken Latin America and Caribbean in Miami, a unit of Heineken N.V., has named a joint venture of Upmarket Illustra in San Francisco and Burkhardt &amp; Partners in New York to handle the creative portion of its account, with billings estimated at $10 million over three years. Those duties had been handled on a project basis by Upmarket, which is headed by Robert Gordon.</p>
        <p>Media buying continues to be handled by various agencies. The Wells Rich Greene BDDP unit of BDDP Group in New York continues as the lead Heineken agency.</p>
        <p>THE MEDIA BUSINESS: ADVERTISING -- ADDENDA</p>
      </block>
